result.execSummary:
The defendant Robert J. Moungey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st Degree Child Sexual Assault - Intercourse with Person under 12 [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class B felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Shall undergo sex offender assessment and follow through with any recommendations;  Shall undergo and follow through with any counseling and/or treatment as directed by agent

Shall have no contact or communication with anyone under the age of 18 without prior approval, including defendant's children and grandchildren; Shall not become involved in activities that include children; Shall not use a computer or any internet capable device without approval; Defendant shall not consume alcohol or other intoxicants.  Defendant must maintain absolute sobriety and shall not go upon the premises of any establishment whose primary business activity involves the sale or distribution of alcoholic beverages, including bars, taverns, liquor stores and beer tents.  Shall not use or possess controlled substances without a legal prescription therefor;  Shall not use or possess drug paraphernalia.
Shall submit a DNA sample; Shall undergo random urinalysis;   Shall register and comply with Sex Offender Registry
